The tone is spot on, the item itself is all right, and the incident write-up certainly adds insight into the consequences of containment failure… but it's too long to upvote. I got partway through the acquisition, scrolled down, saw the rest of the article, and oh dear gods. I did finish it, though, which says a lot about the writing.

Anyway, I suggest getting rid of the acquisition that takes up the last three paragraphs of the Description (which is not where an acquisition belongs anyway), and lopping some of the less interesting details in the Addendum. Oh, and try splitting long paragraphs into two or more smaller ones— carriage returns can do wonders breaking up walls of text. Make the article look less intimidating, and I'll upvote it.







