It's a great idea, it really is. However, it is very, very long. Brevity is a wonderful thing. If this thing breaches containment and some poor sod is handed this article to get himself acquainted with the item before it… I dunno, summons a horde of corpses or something (I didn't quite get that…)… the poor guy is gonna be like 'Wu teh fuh, Foundation. I can't do anything with this!'

Another example. If you are in college, or are headed into college, your teachers are gonna ask for certain page limits. One of my teachers' friends wrote a wonderful story for a class. The page limit was 10. He wrote 15 pages. The teacher flipped through and tore off the extra five pages, then told him that the project was incomplete because he didn't finish the story in ten pages.

In short, long windedness is wonderful in some circles. (I love elaborating on points!) This is not one of those circles. If you want to write a novel, wait until November.







