09 Feb 2011 15:20






So I'm reading this, and thinking "either this has been improved or I was too critical last night." Either way, I like the improved version…

…until the addendum. It is WAY too long and has WAY too much excessive detail about things that really just don't matter for the SCP. It reads like…not even an incident report. It reads like a horror novel (albeit not a very scary one). I would almost completely axe that entire addendum, and shorten it to something like "During the escape of SCP-blockblockblock, a number of corpses were created and adhered to SCP-555. In one case, a D-class with non-functioning legs was drawn to it while still alive. Measures were taken to…" you get the idea. Cut out all the description of the fights, cut out the "heroic measures", cut out the removal of his trachea, etc. It is all unnecessary to the understanding of the SCP, which is what the report should be; enough information for someone reading it to know what it does and how to act around it.

But yeah, besides that, a few other less serious nitpicks…

The 447 reference I think takes away from the rest of the article. 447, while brilliant, is also somewhat goofy, and takes away from the serious tone of this report simply by associating them.

As others have stated, you really need to trim a lot of the fat from this report. Though I suppose your containment procedures are scientifically sound, they seem excessive and overexplained. You run into the same problem with people who love firearms; yes they are cool, and we are happy that you can write lots about them. The problem is, we have almost no idea what you are talking about, so we might as well be reading gibberish. I'm not saying dumb it down to nothing, but a simpler explanation wouldn't hurt.

Sorry for the long post, but yeah, here it is. If you can fix some of the aforementioned issues, it would go a long way.





