… notice how that's so much shorter? We don't need the name of the original deceased, or his date of death (aside from year), or the fact that his gravestone and the cemetery records agreed…

We examined the corpse, so the exhumation is a given. How the SCP was removed from the corpse - who cares? That it wasn't embalmed - how is that relevant?

The fact that other coffins were being drawn towards the SCP - that's useful. What happened to the cemetery after we learned that - we don't care.

See?

Oh, and it really bugs me when our exclusion zones have no margin of safety.

This thing's influence reaches over twelve meters? Then the exclusion zone should be at least fifteen  meters.







